<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-03-0020 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation, to which was referredthe bill (H.R. 940) to implement the provisions of Annex V to the InternationalConvention for the Prevention of Pollution from Ships, 1973, and forother purposes, having considered the same, reports favorably thereonwith an amendment in the nature of a substitute and recommends that thebill as amended do pass. H.R. 940, as reported, provides domestic implementationfor Annex V, Regulations for the Prevention of Pollution by Garbage fromShips, an Optional Annex to the International Convention for the Preventionof Pollution from Ships, 1973 (Convention), as modified by the 1978 Protocolrelating to the Convention (MARPOL Protocol). The bill also initiatesa public-education program and makes additional changes to the Act toPrevent Pollution from Ships (33 U.S.C. 1901 et seq.).</TEXT></DOC>